# Legacy reference code

`api/` (Express + SQLite, ran on a VPS) and `web/` (Vite + React SPA) are the **superseded original app** — read-only parity reference. The live app is the Next.js project at the repo root.

## Runtime constraints

- `api/`: Node ESM Express server with a local SQLite file (`api/data/meavo.db`) and its own Google-token auth — none of this exists in production anymore.
- `web/`: Vite SPA that talked to the Express API; its pages were ported to `src/components/clock-pages/*.jsx`.

## Do NOT

- Treat these trees as the system of record — production is Neon Postgres via `@meavo/db`
- Port new features here — implement in `src/lib/clock/` + `src/app/api/` instead
- Copy the SQLite schema or `admin_allowlist` auth model into the live app

## Porting workflow

1. Find behaviour in `api/src/*.js` (or `web/src/pages/*.jsx`)
2. Implement in `src/lib/clock/` (domain) and `src/app/api/` (routes)
3. Document the mapping in `docs/domain.md` legacy port index
